                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/933: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-06-10T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 10, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>17. The President desires me to send you the following message: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Very glad to have your Number 14 and that you are continuing pressing
                            early adjournment. Perhaps it would be worthwhile considering a motion
                            on Monday or Tuesday stating it is the sense of Conference that its work
                            be concluded on or before August 12th. I think nearly all smaller
                            nations would support this.</p>
                        <p>Congress is in parliamentary difficulties about veterans’ allowances. I
                            still hope for adjournment late tonight. If this not possible am asking
                            for adjournment Monday.</p>
                        <p>My best to you all. (Signed) Roosevelt.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
